column5: I am looking for private cabins that are rented out in the Wiley Point area and north of Wiley
Good luck finding one in that area. Maybe check out the new one that Totem has thats south of Wiley. French Portage.It is new for this upcoming season Good fishen Rob
There's a guy here on WC that has one on Lobstick or Regina Bay, dlhomes is his user name. Bellbuoy

Sorry, didn't want to rain on your parade. I'm from Wpg. and also guide on the lake. I can tell you that from what I know about LOW, what I see on the lake & what I have read in the local papers - renting a cabin on that part of the lake (I think) maybe almost impossible. However now that I said that, yes you can rent, but be prepared to spend a ton o'cash for this rental. I have seen cabins advertised for rent in this area in the 2 - 3 Thousand $$ range, per week. I have also seen cheaper (?) in the 5 thousand range (monthly rental) I dunno, maybe you can afford this ? Do a google and hunt out a local realtor - they should be able to help you or point you in the right direction. I just suggested the new Totem one south of Wiley, it may suit your needs / budget. It is something new & different for Totem. You do it all yourself there. As suggested renting on Regina / Lobstick may be available - but it's one heck of a boat ride out to the Wiley area ! Kelsey Grammer is building a new place out on the west side of Crescent Island, maybe he'll put you up for a stay ? :-} Good Fishen Rob p.s I have friends who have places in this area, I'll ask around & maybe something will pop up.
pm me with your email address i have a cabin in the area
cbprov will even mark you a few spots manitoba .... a 100,000 lakes how many walleyes ???? i will never have enough time....
